elocity remains the same regardless of the slope you are running on. This makes sense from a programming standpoint since the server doesn't want to do this calculation:<br>
sqrt((x1-x2)^2+(y1-y2)^2+(z1-z2)^2)<br>
everytime someone moves.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
First off, the easiest thing to do is to store the max squared run speed instead of the base runspeed.  That eliminates the (costly) sqrt call.  That leaves you with 8 single-cycle operations - not bad, considering what else they have going on.  That isn't, however, what they do, as it is slower to run uphill than downhill.<br>
<br>
Don't believe me?  Find a hill (the steeper, the more noticeable the effect).  Run up it.  If it's a steep enough slope, your forward movement will slow to a crawl.  Now, run down the slope.  Much much faster.  If you're feeling suspicious of your perceptions, go ahead and time it, and do the math. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.emailToFriend?topicID=9057.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.threadControl?topicID=9057.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=9057.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=9057.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies">Training Studio<option value="thesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers">The Back Alley<option value="thesafehousefrm13">Quests of Norrath<option value="thesafehousetherootcellar">The